Contact Book Application
A simple command-line contact book in Python to manage contacts.

Features
Add Contact: Add a new contact with name, phone number, and email.
View Contacts: Display all contacts.
Search Contact: Search for a contact by name.
Update Contact: Update an existing contact's details.
Delete Contact: Remove a contact by name.
Save and Exit: Save changes to contacts.json and exit.
Prerequisites
Python 3.x
Installation
Clone the repository or download the script.
Create a contacts.json file with initial data (optional):
json
Copy code
{
    "John Doe": {
        "phone": "123-456-7890",
        "email": "john.doe@example.com"
    },
    "Jane Smith": {
        "phone": "987-654-3210",
        "email": "jane.smith@example.com"
    }
}
Usage
Run the script:

bash
Copy code
python contact_book.py
Follow the on-screen menu to interact with the contact book.

Example contacts.json
json
Copy code
{
    "John Doe": {
        "phone": "123-456-7890",
        "email": "john.doe@example.com"
    },
    "Jane Smith": {
        "phone": "987-654-3210",
        "email": "jane.smith@example.com"
    }
}
